did.abstract: Business Services exists to perform functions necessary to support the goals of Central Washington University. The services are twofold: those mandated by the external environment and those that provide specific services which directly support the goals of the University.

bioghist.head: Historical Note
bioghist.p: Central Washington University began as the Washington State Normal School in 1891. In 1937, the school was rechristened the Central Washington College of Education. In 1961, the school became Central Washington State College and, finally, in 1977, Central Washington University. This collection documents the financial affairs office of Central Washington University through the years of 1902 to 2016.

scopecontent.p: This collection includes maps, documents, and ledgers related to the business and financial affairs office of Central Washington University. The documents include committee meeting minutes, newspaper clippings, and documents showing the local community and campus over time.

accessrestrict.p: Open to the public for education research.
